-- PBG CEO Sees Polish State Fund’s Decision on Loan in 6 Months
-- B y   M a r t a   W a l d o c h   a n d   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-08-01T07:40:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-01/pbg-ceo-sees-polish-state-fund-s-decision-on-loan-in-6-months.html
PBG SA (PBG) , the Polish builder under
bankruptcy protection from creditors, which filed for a loan
from ARP state fund to finance operations, expects ARP decision
“no sooner” than in six months, Chief Executive Officer
Wieslaw Rozacki said in an interview with TVN CNBC.  Rozacki added that “it is possible” its unit  Hydrobudowa
Polska SA (HBP)  may file for a liquidation bankruptcy.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Marta Waldoch in Warsaw at 
